liblingoteach
------------------------------------------
LibLingoTeach is a C library using libXML to access the XML lesson files
provided by the LingoTeach project. It can read and write lessons, manipulate
the meanings and translations hold by those and many more. It uses the
LingoTeach DTD specification to validate the files and operates on the data in
various ways. Due to the way the data is hold in memory, it is possible to
operate on detailled subsets of a specific lesson.

Runtime requirements:
  cygwin-3.5.4-1
  liblingoteach-devel-0.2.3-1bl4
  liblingoteach4-0.2.3-1bl4
  libxml2-2.10.4-2
  libxml2-devel-2.10.4-2
  pkg-config-2.3.0-1

Build requirements:
(besides corresponding -devel packages)
  autoconf-15-2
  automake-20240607-1
  binutils-2.43.1-1
  cygport-0.36.9-1
  gcc-core-12.4.0-3
  libtool-2.5.3-1
  libxml2-devel-2.10.4-2
  make-4.4.1-2

Canonical website:
  https://sourceforge.net/projects/lingoteach/

Canonical download:
  mirror://sourceforge/lingoteach/liblingoteach-0.2.3.tar.gz

-------------------------------------------

Build instructions:
  1. unpack liblingoteach-0.2.3-X-src.tar.xz
  2. if you use setup to install this src package,
     it will be unpacked under /usr/src automatically
        % cd /usr/src
        % cygport ./liblingoteach-0.2.3-X.cygport all

This will create:
  /usr/src/liblingoteach-0.2.3-X-src.tar.xz
  /usr/src/liblingoteach-0.2.3-X.tar.xz
  /usr/src/liblingoteach4-0.2.3-X.tar.xz
  /usr/src/liblingoteach-devel-0.2.3-X.tar.xz

-------------------------------------------

Files included in the binary package:

(liblingoteach)
  /usr/share/doc/Cygwin/liblingoteach.README
  /usr/share/doc/liblingoteach/AUTHORS
  /usr/share/doc/liblingoteach/COPYING
  /usr/share/doc/liblingoteach/ChangeLog
  /usr/share/doc/liblingoteach/HACKING
  /usr/share/doc/liblingoteach/NEWS
  /usr/share/doc/liblingoteach/README

(liblingoteach4)
  /usr/bin/cyglingoteach-4.dll

(liblingoteach-devel)
  /usr/include/lingoteach/lingdefs.h
  /usr/include/lingoteach/lingoteach.h
  /usr/lib/liblingoteach.dll.a
  /usr/lib/pkgconfig/liblingoteach.pc

